  "prompt": "Which are the top five pilot training institutes in India and why?",
  "response": "The top five pilot training institutes in India are identified based on their reputation, the quality of training programs they offer, infrastructure, experienced faculty, and placement records. These institutes are:\n\n1. **Indira Gandhi Institute of Aeronautics (IGIA), Chandigarh**:\n   - IGIA offers comprehensive pilot training programs and has a well-structured curriculum.\n   - The institute is known for experienced faculty and state-of-the-art training equipment.\n   - It has strong industry connections which help in better placement opportunities for students.\n\n2. **Rajiv Gandhi Aviation Academy, Hyderabad**:\n   - One of the oldest and most prestigious pilot training institutes in India.\n   - Offers DGCA-approved courses and advanced simulators.\n   - The academy has a high placement record and strong industry links.\n\n3. **Bombay Flying Club, Mumbai**:\n   - Established in 1928, it's one of the most reputed flying clubs in India.\n   - Provides extensive training with modern facilities and experienced instructors.\n   - Known for its rigorous training programs that meet international standards.\n\n4. **CAE Oxford Aviation Academy, Gondia**:\n   - Part of the global CAE network, known for high-quality pilot training programs.\n   - Offers advanced training infrastructure and an extensive fleet.\n   - Strong focus on skill development with excellent placement records in top airlines.\n\n5. **Indira Gandhi Rashtriya Uran Akademi (IGRUA), Rae Bareli**:\n   - Established in 1985, IGRUA is renowned for its high standards in pilot training.\n   - Government-funded institute with excellent training facilities and experienced faculty.\n   - Known for its rigorous training programs and high placement rates in various airlines.\n\nThese institutes stand out due to their high-quality training programs, modern infrastructure, skilled instructors, and strong placement records, making them top choices for aspiring pilots in India.",
